Together we wrote a no_std rust app that uses syscalls crate to make small linux apps. The test app I called rust-main-no-std results in 1040 byte binary. One small catch, vscode is configured to use clangd, we might want to verify that instead of MS Intellisense, and it's is reporting an error:
```
error[E0152]: found duplicate lang item `panic_impl`
  --> src/main.rs:66:1
   |
66 | / fn panic(_: &PanicInfo) -> ! {
67 | |     exit(1);
68 | | }
   | |_^
   |
   = note: the lang item is first defined in crate `std` (which `test` depends on)
   = note: first definition in `std` loaded from /home/wink/.rustup/toolchains/stable-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/lib/rustlib/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/lib/libstd-210854cf1daa4bec.rlib
   = note: second definition in the local crate (`rust_main_no_std`)
```
`cargo check` doesn't have an issue:
```
$ cargo clean ; cargo check
     Removed 110 files, 19.9MiB total
   Compiling syscalls v0.7.0
    Checking rust-main-no-std v0.1.0 (/home/wink/data/prgs/rust/rust-main-no-std)
    Finished `dev` profile [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.47s
```
Here is the code:
```
#![no_std]
#![no_main]

use core::panic::PanicInfo;
use syscalls::{syscall3, Sysno};

mod shims;

const STDIN: usize = 0;
const STDOUT: usize = 1;

#[unsafe(no_mangle)]
#[unsafe(naked)]
pub extern "C" fn _start() -> ! {
    // Kernel enters with RSP = 16n
    core::arch::naked_asm!(
        "mov  rbx, rsp",            // save original RSP (points to argc)
        "mov  rdi, [rbx]",          // rdi = argc (u64)
        "lea  rsi, [rbx+8]",        // rsi = &argv[0]
        "lea  rdx, [rsi + rdi*8 + 8]", // rdx = &envp[0] = &argv[argc] + 1 (skip NULL)
        "call {rust_main}",         // callee entry sees RSP % 16 == 8
        "ud2",
        rust_main = sym rust_main,
    );
}

fn rust_main(argc: usize,
             _argv: *const *const u8,
             _envp: *const *const u8) -> ! {
    let mut buf = [0u8; 128];
    let s = "argc=";
    let n = s.len();

    _ = unsafe { syscall3(Sysno::write, STDOUT, s.as_ptr() as usize, n).ok(); };
    buf[0] = argc as u8 + 0x30;
    buf[1] = b'\n';
    _ = unsafe { syscall3(Sysno::write, STDOUT, buf.as_mut_ptr() as usize, 2).ok(); };

    loop {
        // read from stdin
        let n = unsafe {
            syscall3(Sysno::read, STDIN, buf.as_mut_ptr() as usize, buf.len())
                .unwrap_or(0)
        };

        if n == 0 {
            // EOF -> exit
            exit(0);
        }

        // echo to stdout
        unsafe {
            syscall3(Sysno::write, STDOUT, buf.as_ptr() as usize, n).ok();
        }
    }
}

fn exit(code: usize) -> ! {
    unsafe {
        syscalls::syscall1(Sysno::exit, code).ok();
    }
    loop {}
}

#[panic_handler]
fn panic(_: &PanicInfo) -> ! {
    exit(1);
}
```
